         <p>For content that does not exist in the SSP, the SAP tool must ensure an ID is used that
            is both unique in the SAP and does not exist in the SSP.</p>
         <p>When the same ID is found in both the SSP and the SAP, the SAP tool should treat the
            associated content in the SAP as adding to or overriding the content in the SSP. (This
            is how assessors correct inaccurate SSP content without changing the SSP itself.)</p>
         <p>When missing or incorrect SSP content needs to be added to the SAP, the SAP tool should
            place the content in the SAP as follows:</p>
         <ul>
            <li>Components: local-definitions</li>
            <li>Inventory Items: local-definitions</li>
            <li>User Roles: local-definitions</li>
